# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SPECTER Indexer (Envio) — Environment Variables Reference
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values. Never commit .env.

# ─── Turso (libSQL) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The SPECTER API registry database that the indexer writes announcement events to.
# Must match the TURSO_DATABASE_URL / TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN in specter/.env — both
# services share the same DB so the API can read what the indexer writes.
# Get credentials from: https://turso.tech → your database → Generate Token
TURSO_DATABASE_URL=libsql://your-db-name.turso.io
TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-turso-auth-token-here

# ─── Envio Local Ports ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Hasura GraphQL API is exposed on 8181 instead of the default 8080 because
# 8080 is taken by the SPECTER-web Vite dev server when running concurrently.
HASURA_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:8181/v1/metadata
HASURA_EXTERNAL_PORT=8181

# ─── Turso Retry Worker ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The retrySync worker queries Envio's Hasura GraphQL for events where
# tursoSynced=false and re-pushes them to Turso. Tune these if events lag.

# GraphQL endpoint for Envio's local Hasura instance.
# Derived automatically from HASURA_EXTERNAL_PORT if not set here.
# Only override if Hasura runs on a non-standard host or port.
# ENVIO_GRAPHQL_URL=http://localhost:8181/v1/graphql

# How often the retry cycle runs (milliseconds). Default: 300000 (5 minutes).
# Increase for cost savings if events are infrequent; decrease for lower latency.
# TURSO_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS=300000

# Maximum number of unsynced events to fetch and retry per cycle. Default: 5000.
# If you consistently hit this limit, consider running a full re-index or
# increasing this value to clear the backlog faster.
# TURSO_RETRY_MAX_FETCH=5000

# ─── Monad RPC Override (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Envio uses HyperSync for Monad by default — no RPC key is needed.
# Only set this if you need to override the public HyperSync endpoint.
# MONAD_RPC_URL=https://testnet-rpc.monad.xyz

# ─── Envio Hosted Service (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed when deploying to Envio's hosted indexing service (envio.dev).
# Get from: https://envio.dev → your project → Settings
# ENVIO_API_TOKEN=your-envio-api-token
